## ğŸ›  Usage

Launch the CLI:

```bash
another-sender
```

Or check the version:

```bash
another-sender --version
```

---

## ğŸ§© Menu Options

- `A` â€“ Send all files in the selected folder
- `T` â€“ Set delay (in seconds) between sending each line
- `C` â€“ Change active command folder (`commands/`)
- `M` â€“ Change communication mode (`UDP`, `SPI`, `I2C`)
- `P` â€“ Change parser type (`text`, `hex`, `json`)
- Select a file number to send a specific file
- `Q` â€“ Quit

---

## ğŸ§¾ Command File Format

Command files are plain text and support:
- Blank lines and `#` comments (ignored)
- Commands interpreted based on parser type

### Example (`text`)
```txt
# type: text
PING
RESET
START
```

### Example (`hex`)
```txt
01 FF A0 0D
02 00 3B
```

---

## ğŸ”„ Persistent Config

Stored in:

- `command.meta.json`
  - Communication mode
  - Parser type
  - Command folder
- `udp_config.json`
  - IP address and port
  - Delay setting

